overview: Five immigrant women from four different countries: Brazil, Romania, Italy, and Turkey navigate expectations, stereotypes, and cultural shocks in the United States, all while trying to hold on to their own identity. Through a series of sketches and a few short scenes based on real conversations, the women poke fun at peopleâ€™s preconceived notions about their cultures, but also raise important questions regarding their status in the US.
title: None of the Above
